'''Ramy Hisham Abdel Aziz Mostafa Rabia''' ({{langx|ar|رامي هشام عبد العزيز مصطفى ربيعة}}; born 20 May 1993) is an Egyptian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[UAE Pro League]] club [[Al Ain FC|Al Ain]] and the [[Egypt national football team|Egypt national team]].

He began his career with [[Al Ahly SC|Al Ahly]], making his professional debut at the age of seventeen in 2010. Regarded as one of the brightest prospects in Egyptian football,<ref name="fiat">{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2015/05/01/driving-your-ferrami-like-a-fiat-the-curious-case-of-rami-rabia/ |title=Driving your Ferrami like a FIAT: The curious case of Rami Rabia |website=KingFut.com |first=Ahmed |last=Assem |date=1 May 2015 |access-date=28 July 2018}}</ref> he attracted attention from several clubs before joining Portuguese side [[Sporting Clube de Portugal|Sporting CP]] in 2014 for a fee of €750,000. However, after one season in which he made only three first team appearances, he rejoined Al Ahly.

==Early life==
Rabia was born in [[Cairo]], Egypt on 20 May 1993.<ref name="Soccerway">{{Soccerway|168474|access-date=29 July 2018}}</ref> He started his football career at Al Ahly's academy.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ramy Rabia ( Ramy Rabia) |url=https://misrconnect.com/en/profiles/932 |access-date=2024-10-27 |website=misrconnect.com |language=en}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Al Ahly===
[[File:RamyRabia2011.jpg|thumb|Ramy Rabia with Al Ahly in 2011]]
Rabia began his career with [[Al Ahly SC|Al Ahly]], making his debut against [[Haras El Hodoud SC|Haras El Hodoud]] under coach [[Abdul-Aziz Abdul-Shafi]] at the age of seventeen due to injuries to several first team players.<ref name="fiat"/><ref name="focused">{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2013/05/17/egypts-rabia-focused-on-u20-world-cup-despite-chelsea-manchester-united-links/ |title=Egypt's Rabia focused on U20 World Cup despite Chelsea, Manchester United links |website=KingFut.com |date=17 May 2013 |access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref> Despite Abduk-Shafi's departure soon after, Rabia continued in the first team under new manager [[Manuel José de Jesus]].<ref name="fiat"/> After club captain [[Hossam Ghaly]] was ruled out with injury, Rabia was chosen as his replacement as a defensive midfielder during the [[2013 FIFA Club World Cup]] in Morocco. He earned praise for his performances during the tournament and the club's subsequent league matches as he helped the club win the [[Egyptian Premier League]] title after overcoming a seven-point deficit to rivals [[Zamalek SC|Zamalek]].<ref name="fiat"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2013/06/22/player-profile-rami-rabia/ |title=Player Profile: Rami Rabia |website=KingFut.com |first=Mohamed |last=Al-Hendy |date=22 June 2013 |access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref> He attracted attention from several European sides, including [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]], [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] and [[Borussia Dortmund]]. He was offered a trial with French side [[Lille OSC|Lille]] but was forced to cancel after undergoing surgery for a knee injury suffered during a league match against [[Smouha SC|Smouha]].<ref name="focused"/>

In December 2013, English [[Premier League]] club [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] submitted an offer for Rabia to join the club on a trial period with the possibility of a loan move for the remainder of the 2013–14 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/6/51/89717/Sports/Egyptian-Football/Hull-City-interested-in-signing-Ahly-youngster-on-.aspx |title=Hull City interested in signing Ahly youngster on loan |publisher=Ahram Online |date=21 December 2013 |access-date=14 September 2018}}</ref> The club had previously approached Al Ahly prior to the Club World Cup but negotiations had been delayed to allow Rabia to take part in the competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2013/12/20/hull-city-to-loan-al-ahly-rami-rabia/ |title=Hull City request to loan Al Ahly youngster Rami Rabia |website=KingFut.com |first=Marwan |last=Ahmed |date=20 December 2013 |access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref> However, Al Ahly rejected the offer with club director Sayed Adbel-Hafiz stating "We totally refuse the idea of a player going out on loan from Al Ahly to a club that does not know if they will sign him or not."<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2013/12/21/al-ahly-reject-hull-citys-trial-offer-rabia/ |title=Al Ahly reject Hull City offer for Rami Rabia |website=KingFut.com |first=Marwan |last=Ahmed |date=21 December 2013 |access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref> Despite the move being called off, Hull manager [[Steve Bruce]] described Rabia as having "a big future ahead of him."<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2013/12/21/steve-bruce-rami-rabia-big-future/ |title=Steve Bruce: Rami Rabia 'has a big future’ |website=KingFut.com |date=21 December 2013 |access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref>

During his first spell with Al Ahly, Rabia helped the side win two Egyptian Premier League titles, two [[CAF Champions League]] titles and two [[CAF Super Cup]]s.<ref name="farewell">{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2014/08/04/rabias-sends-message-al-ahly-fans/ |title=Rami Rabia writes open farewell letter to Al Ahly fans |website=KingFut.com |first=Nouran |last=Hegazy |date=4 August 2014 |access-date=27 July 2018}}</ref> Ramy Rabia is an Egyptian defender who currently plays for Al-Ahly in the Egyptian Premier League.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ramy Rabia - biography, stats, rating, footballer’s profile {{!}} Football Top.com |url=https://www.footballtop.com/players/ramy-rabia |access-date=2024-10-27 |website=www.footballtop.com}}</ref>

===Sporting CP===
In May 2014, Portuguese side [[Sporting Clube de Portugal|Sporting CP]] submitted several offers for Rabia, starting at €250,000 and rising to €550,000, which were both rejected by Al Ahly who valued the player at €1.5 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2014/05/31/sporting-lisbon-increases-offer-rami-rabia/ |title=Sporting Lisbon improve offer for Rami Rabia |website=KingFut.com |first=Alexandre |last=Queirós |date=31 May 2014 |access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2014/06/12/al-ahly-set-rami-rabia-price/ |title=Al Ahly set Ramy Rabia price for Sporting Lisbon |website=KingFut.com |first=Alexandre |last=Queirós |date=12 June 2014 |access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref> Al Ahly director [[Wael Gomaa]] urged Rabia to focus on his commitments to the club and ignore any transfer approaches.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2014/07/20/gomaa-rabiaa-commit-contract/ |title=Gomaa: I would like Rabia to commit to his contract |website=KingFut.com |first=Abdelrahman |last=Amr |date=20 July 2014 |access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref> However, a transfer was eventually completed in a deal worth around €750,000 with Al Ahly set to earn 15% of any future transfer. Rabia joined the club on a six-year contract with a €45 million release clause.<ref>{{cite web|website=King Fut.com|title=Exclusive: Egypt’s Rami Rabia signs for Sporting Lisbon|url=http://www.kingfut.com/2014/07/23/egypts-rami-rabia-signs-sporting-lisbon/|date=23 July 2014 |access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2014/08/09/official-rami-rabia-moves-sporting-lisbon/ |title=Rami Rabia moves to Sporting Lisbon |website=KingFut.com |first=Ahmad |last=Yousef |date=9 August 2014 |access-date=27 July 2018}}</ref> Following his departure, he released a statement to the club's fans, commenting "Al Ahly is the love of my life."<ref name="farewell"/>

On his arrival at Sporting, Rabia joined the club's reserve side, [[Sporting CP B]]. He made his debut for the side in a 3–0 victory over [[C.D. Aves|Aves]] in the [[Segunda Liga]] and provided an assist for [[Lewis Enoh]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2014/08/27/video-rami-rabia-stars-sporting-b-win/ |title=Rami Rabia stars in Sporting B win |website=KingFut.com |first=Andrew |last=Finn |date=27 August 2014 |access-date=27 July 2018}}</ref> However, Rabia was forced to undergo surgery on his stomach after his debut to fix a longstanding problem.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/6/53/109764/Sports/Talents-Abroad/Sportings-Rabiea-out-for-five-weeks.aspx |title=Sporting's Rabiea out for five weeks |publisher=Ahram Online |date=1 September 2014 |access-date=14 September 2018}}</ref> He had been playing with the injury for a month but stated that he could not "take the pain anymore."<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2014/09/01/exclusive-rabia-to-undergo-surgery/ |title=Rami Rabia to undergo surgery on Tuesday night |website=KingFut.com |first=Marwan |last=Ahmed |date=1 September 2014 |access-date=27 July 2018}}</ref> After missing five weeks due to the surgery, Rabia returned to the club's reserve side but received criticism from Sporting manager [[Marco Silva]] after being deemed at fault for two goals during a 5–0 defeat against [[Atlético CP]]. Silva described Rabia as being "in a very delayed stage of his evolution as a player."<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2014/11/08/sporting-coach-rabia-evolve/ |title=Sporting coach: Rabia needs to evolve as a player |website=KingFut.com |first=Alexandre |last=Queirós |date=8 November 2014 |access-date=28 July 2018}}</ref>

In January 2015, Rabia made his debut for Sporting's first team in a 1–0 victory over [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] in the [[Taça de Portugal]], a knockout cup competition, as a late substitute in place of [[Ryan Gauld]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2015/01/15/rabia-debuts-sporting-cup-win-boavista/ |title=Rabia debuts for Sporting in Portuguese League Cup win over Boavista |website=KingFut.com |author=Ahmed Yasser Othman |date=15 January 2015 |access-date=28 July 2018}}</ref> He made his first start for the club in the first leg of the following round, a 3–2 defeat to [[C.F. Os Belenenses|Belenenses]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2015/01/22/rami-rabia-plays-first-official-90-minutes-sportings-3-2-defeat/ |title=Rami Rabia plays first official 90 minutes in Sporting’s 3-2 defeat |website=KingFut.com |first=Mohamed |last=Osama |date=22 January 2015 |access-date=28 July 2018}}</ref> In total, he made three first team appearances for Sporting during the season, all in the Taça de Portugal.<ref name="Soccerway"/>

===Return to Al Ahly===
After being sent to train with Sporting's reserve side during preseason prior to the 2015–16 season, Rabia announced his intention to leave Sporting either permanently or on loan.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2015/07/09/exclusive-rami-rabia-leaving-sporting/ |title=Rami Rabia to KingFut: I’m leaving Sporting |website=KingFut.com |first=Marwan |last=Ahmed |date=9 July 2015 |access-date=29 July 2018}}</ref> In August 2015, he rejoined his former club Al Ahly on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/6/51/139349/Sports/Egyptian-Football/Ahly-bring-back-defender-Rabia-from-Sporting-Lisbo.aspx |title=Ahly bring back defender Rabia from Sporting Lisbon |publisher=Ahram Online |date=31 August 2015 |access-date=14 September 2018}}</ref> Al Ahly paid €750,000 to resign Rabia, the same amount he was sold for the previous season, with Sporting also set to receive 15% of any future transfer fee.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2015/08/31/rami-rabia-rejoins-al-ahly/ |title=Rami Rabia rejoins Al Ahly on five-year deal |website=KingFut.com |first=Salma |last=Abdallah |date=31 August 2015 |access-date=29 July 2018}}</ref>

During the 2016–17 season, Rabia struggled to maintain his place in the side after suffering several injury setbacks. He was forced to undergo knee surgery in August 2016, initially expected to keep him out for one month,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2016/08/21/rabia-rule-one-month/ |title=Rami Rabia ruled out for one month |website=KingFut.com |first=Abdelrahman |last=Amr |date=21 August 2016 |access-date=29 July 2018}}</ref> and needed a second operation on the injury the following month.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2016/09/28/rami-rabia-undergo-second-knee-operation/ |title=Rabi Ramia to undergo second knee operation |website=KingFut.com |first=Marwan |last=Ahmed |date=28 September 2016 |access-date=29 July 2018}}</ref> After recovering from surgery, Rabia made two appearances for Al Ahly before experiencing a further setback after colliding with goalkeeper [[Ahmed Adel Abdel Moneam]] in training and suffering ankle ligament damage.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2016/12/26/rami-rabia-miss-afcon/ |title=Rami Rabia to miss AFCON due to injury |website=KingFut.com |first=Seif |last=Soliman |date=26 December 2016 |access-date=29 July 2018}}</ref> His injury troubles continued the following season, suffering a groin injury during an international match in November 2017,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2017/11/13/rami-rabia-groin-injury/ |title=Rami Rabia reveals the extent of groin injury |website=KingFut.com |first=Abdelrahman |last=Amr |date=13 November 2017 |access-date=29 July 2018}}</ref> missing ten matches. In January 2018, he again suffered a groin injury during a league match against rivals Zamalek and was ruled out for two months.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/6/0/288150/Sports/0/Ahlys-Rabia-out-for-weeks-with-muscle-injury.aspx |title=Ahly's Rabia out for weeks with muscle injury |publisher=Ahram Online |date=14 January 2018 |access-date=14 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2018/01/14/rami-rabia-two-months-groin/ |title=Rami Rabia ruled out for at least two months with groin injury |website=KingFut.com |first=Seif |last=Soliman |date=14 January 2018 |access-date=29 July 2018}}</ref> After missing the remainder of the season, Rabia was forced to publicly deny reports that he could be forced to retire due to ongoing injury problems, commenting "I can’t say when I will return, it takes time."<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2018/07/23/rabia-injury-recover/ |title=Al Ahly defeat Rami Rabia rejects retirement talk |website=KingFut.com |first=Ramez |last=Nathan |date=23 July 2018 |access-date=29 July 2018}}</ref>

Rabia left the club at the end of the 2024–25 season, having accumulated a total of 337 appearances.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2025/06/03/official-ramy-rabia-joins-uae-giants-al-ain/ |title=OFFICIAL: Ramy Rabia Joins UAE Giants Al Ain |publisher=KingFut |date=3 June 2025 }}</ref>

===Al Ain===
In June 2025, Rabia joined [[UAE Pro League]] side [[Al Ain FC|Al Ain]] as a free agent.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://alainclub.ae/fc/ramy-rabia-joining-al-ain-football-club-is-a-turning-point-in-my-professional-football-career-i-am-also-feeling-proud-for-being-affiliated-to-the-ainawi-nation/ |title=Ramy Rabia: Joining Al Ain football club is a turning point in my professional football career.. I am also feeling proud for being affiliated to the Ainawi nation |publisher=Al Ain FC |access-date=8 June 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth teams===
Rabia represented Egypt at [[Egypt national under-20 football team|under-20 level]], captaining the side to victory in the [[2013 African U-20 Championship]]. He scored the goal that confirmed the squad's qualification for the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] with a header during a 1–0 victory over [[Algeria national under-20 football team|Algeria]] and sent the side through to the semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2013/03/20/video-captain-rami-rabia-heads-egypt-to-u20-world-cup/ |title=Captain Rami Rabia heads Egypt to U20 World Cup |website=KingFut.com |date=20 March 2013 |access-date=25 July 2017}}</ref> He led the side to their fourth tournament title and first since 2003 after defeating [[Ghana national under-20 football team|Ghana]] in the final.<ref name="focused"/> Rabia later represented Egypt at under-23 level, playing in the side's unsuccessful qualifying campaign for the [[Football at the 2016 Summer Olympics|2016 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2015/12/10/rami-rabia-on-olympic-failure/ |title=Rami Rabia sheds light on failure to reach Olympics |website=KingFut.com |first=Marwan |last=Ahmed |date=10 December 2015 |access-date=29 July 2018}}</ref>

Despite still being in recovery after undergoing knee surgery,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/6/52/70558/Sports/National-Teams/Egypt-U-defender-Rabiaa-may-miss-World-Cup.aspx |title=Egypt U-20 defender Rabiaa may miss World Cup |publisher=Ahram Online |first=Eslam |last=Omar |date=2 May 2013 |access-date=14 September 2018}}</ref> Rabia was named in manager [[Rabie Yassin]]'s preliminary squad for the Under-20 World Cup.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2013/05/19/young-pharaohs-coach-rabie-yassin-names-35-man-provisional-squad/ |title=Young Pharaohs coach Rabie Yassin names provisional squad for U-20 World Cup |website=KingFut.com |date=19 May 2013 |access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref> The injury forced Rabia to miss the side's warm up matches prior to the tournament but he returned prior to Egypt's first group match and was appointed captain of the squad, commenting "I only came back a few days before our first game, so I didn’t expect this honor and I know I owe the coach a lot."<ref name="talks">{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2013/06/29/interview-ramy-rabia-talks-epl-wenger-and-captain-responsibilities/ |title=Ramy Rabia talks EPL, Wenger and captain responsibilities – FIFA |website=KingFut.com |first=Mohamed |last=Seif |date=29 June 2013 |access-date=25 July 2017}}</ref> He featured in all three of Egypt's group matches as they were eliminated after finishing third.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2013/06/29/video-egypt-2-0-england-pharoahs-crash-out-of-the-u-20-world-cup/ |title=Egypt 2–0 England Pharaohs Crash Out of U-20 World Cup |website=KingFut.com |date=29 June 2014 |access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref>

===Senior team===
Rabia made his debut for the [[Egypt national football team|Egypt senior team]] under coach [[Bob Bradley]] on 28 December 2012 during a 2–0 victory over [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]].<ref name="nft">{{NFT player|50380|access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref> On 7 March 2013, Rabia scored his first senior international goal in a [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against Qatar, scoring his side's only goal in a 3–1 defeat.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2013/03/07/video-ahly-flavoured-egypt-lose-3-1-to-qatar/ |title=Qatar punish Ahly flavoured Egypt |website=KingFut.com |date=7 March 2013 |access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref> He scored another goal in his following appearance, a 2–0 victory over [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]] before scoring his first competitive goal in 2015 during a 3–0 victory over [[Tanzania national football team|Tanzania]] during the [[2017 Africa Cup of Nations qualification|qualifying rounds]] of the [[2017 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref name="nft"/>

In October 2017, Rabia was part of the Egyptian side that qualified for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], the first time the nation had reached a tournament since 1990, after defeating [[DR Congo national football team|Congo]] 2–1.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/oct/08/world-cup-round-up-egypt-poland-qualify |title=Mo Salah’s late penalty gives Egypt first World Cup qualification since 1990 |newspaper=The Guardian |date=8 October 2017 |access-date=14 September 2018}}</ref> However, his injury problems during the 2017–18 led to him being omitted from Egypt's squad for the tournament.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-cup/0/egypt-world-cup-2018-team-guide-squad-list/ |title=Egypt World Cup 2018 team guide and squad list |newspaper=The Telegraph |date=25 June 2018 |access-date=14 September 2018}}</ref>

On 2 December 2025, Rabia was called up to the Egypt squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/egypt-name-final-28-man-squad-for-totalenergies-caf-afcon-2025-salah-leads-pharaohs-charge/|title=Egypt name final 28-man squad for TotalEnergies CAF AFCON 2025, Salah leads Pharaohs' charge|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=2 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

